HEADWORD: Elocation
<hw>El`o*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>e-</ets> + <ets>locate</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A removal
from the usual place of residence.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Departure from the usual state; an ecstasy.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

